## eBird — Sanity-config-driven fetch client

**Do NOT replace with a community eBird MCP** (moonbirdai/ebird-mcp-server, siansiansu/ebird-mcp-server). No official eBird MCP from Cornell Lab exists. Community MCPs have no awareness of the Sanity-driven config that controls which hotspots, species, and observation window are active.

### Architecture

```
Sanity ebirdBirding document
  └─ mapDataSource  (hotspots | region)
  └─ hotspotCodes   (space/comma-separated L-codes)
  └─ regionCode     (e.g. US-NY-109)
  └─ focusSpeciesCode
  └─ recentDaysBack
  └─ maxObservationsToFetch

resolved at runtime by src/lib/ebird/resolveConfig.ts
  └─ passed to src/lib/ebird/client.ts → fetchMapObservations()
  └─ rendered by src/components/backyard/
```

### Rules

- **Always go through `fetchMapObservations(config)`** — never call the eBird API directly from components.
- Config values come from Sanity. Use the Sanity MCP to update `ebirdBirding` fields (hotspots, species, observation window) rather than editing code.
- The `EBIRD_API_KEY` must be set in `.env.local`.
- eBird observation window is capped at 30 days by the API; `recentDaysBack` must be between 1–30.

### Key files

```
src/lib/ebird/
  client.ts         ← fetchMapObservations() — the only production eBird fetch entry point
  resolveConfig.ts  ← maps Sanity ebirdBirding doc → ResolvedEbirdBirding
  types.ts          ← BirdObservation, EbirdObservationsResult
src/components/backyard/
  BackyardBirdMap.tsx / BackyardBirdMapDynamic.tsx / BackyardBirdMapLoading.tsx
  BackyardObservationsTable.tsx
```

